\title{Example Skill}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{version}{1.0.0}

\meta{description}{This skill should be used when the user asks to "demonstrate skills", "show skill format", "create a skill template", or discusses skill development patterns. Provides a reference template for creating Claude Code plugin skills.}

\subtree{
\title{Example Skill}
\p{This skill demonstrates the structure and format for Claude Code plugin skills.}

\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{Skills are model-invoked capabilities that Claude autonomously uses based on task context. Unlike commands (user-invoked) or agents (spawned by Claude), skills provide contextual guidance that Claude incorporates into its responses.}
}

\subtree{
\title{When This Skill Applies}
\p{This skill activates when the user's request involves:}

\ul{
\li{Creating or understanding plugin skills}
\li{Skill template or reference needs}
\li{Skill development patterns}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Skill Structure}
\subtree{
\title{Required Files}
\pre{\startverb
skills/
└── skill-name/
    └── SKILL.md          # Main skill definition (required)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Optional Supporting Files}
\pre{\startverb
skills/
└── skill-name/
    ├── SKILL.md          # Main skill definition
    ├── README.md         # Additional documentation
    ├── references/       # Reference materials
    │   └── patterns.md
    ├── examples/         # Example files
    │   └── sample.md
    └── scripts/          # Helper scripts
        └── helper.sh
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Frontmatter Options}
\p{Skills support these frontmatter fields:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{name} (required): Skill identifier}
\li{\strong{description} (required): Trigger conditions - describe when Claude should use this skill}
\li{\strong{version} (optional): Semantic version number}
\li{\strong{license} (optional): License information or reference}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Writing Effective Descriptions}
\p{The description field is crucial - it tells Claude when to invoke the skill.}

\p{\strong{Good description patterns:}}

\pre{\startverb
description: This skill should be used when the user asks to "specific phrase", "another phrase", mentions "keyword", or discusses topic-area.
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Include:}}

\ul{
\li{Specific trigger phrases users might say}
\li{Keywords that indicate relevance}
\li{Topic areas the skill covers}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Skill Content Guidelines}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Clear purpose}: State what the skill helps with}
\li{\strong{When to use}: Define activation conditions}
\li{\strong{Structured guidance}: Organize information logically}
\li{\strong{Actionable instructions}: Provide concrete steps}
\li{\strong{Examples}: Include practical examples when helpful}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Best Practices}
\ul{
\li{Keep skills focused on a single domain}
\li{Write descriptions that clearly indicate when to activate}
\li{Include reference materials in subdirectories for complex skills}
\li{Test that the skill activates for expected queries}
\li{Avoid overlap with other skills' trigger conditions}
}
}
}